    "summary": "Bert Kerkman is a Netherlands attorney specialized in Netherlands corporate law, commercial law and insolvency law, and complex cross-border dispute resolution.  A member of the Amsterdam Bar and of the Paris Bar, he has worked as an associate and partner with large Netherlands and U.S. law firms prior to founding his own firm in Amsterdam.\n\nBert has many years of experience representing international businesses regarding their corporate and commercial matters in The Netherlands. His clients are multinational companies, many of which are based in North America and in French speaking jurisdictions , with activities in a variety of industries, including banking and finance, capital goods, aeronautics, and international trade and distribution. \n\nBert received a degree in Dutch Civil Law and Commercial Law from the University of Utrecht Law School, The Netherlands. Post graduate studies were completed at the University of Amsterdam,  Erasmus University of Rotterdam, and Universit\u00e9 du Panth\u00e9on-Assas Paris II. He also obtained the qualification certificate of the Netherlands Association for International Trade Lawyers (NAVIH) as well as the Grotius-Insolad qualification certificate in Netherlands insolvency law. \n\nIn addition to his activities as an attorney, Bert is a substitute Judge in the District Courts of The Netherlands, and acts as an ad-hoc arbitrator in commercial disputes. \n\nBert is a member of the American Bar Association, the Association for International Arbitration (AIA), the  Netherlands association for civil litigation law (NvvP), the Netherlands association for corporate litigation (Vereniging Corporate Litigation), and the association for  distribution, franchise and commercial agency law (DFA).\n\nHe speaks, reads and writes English, French, German, and Dutch professionally, and has knowledge of Spanish, Russian and Afrikaans.",
